1
00:00:06,708 --> 00:00:07,625
[music playing and singing]

2
00:00:07,625 --> 00:00:14,916
♪ ♪

3
00:00:17,041 --> 00:00:19,208
[cheers]

4
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:22,916
[muffled music and singing]

5
00:00:22,916 --> 00:00:27,625
Wait, what'd you say?

6
00:00:27,833 --> 00:00:31,625
We said, stay out
of our way or we'll kill you.

7
00:00:31,833 --> 00:00:33,041
Why are you--

8
00:00:33,250 --> 00:00:34,333
ah!

9
00:00:36,208 --> 00:00:37,166
Oh!

10
00:00:37,375 --> 00:00:38,625
It's no use.

11
00:00:38,625 --> 00:00:40,750
These guys have been
completely brainwashed.

12
00:00:40,958 --> 00:00:43,625
[music playing]

13
00:00:43,625 --> 00:00:44,583
Out of the way!

14
00:00:44,791 --> 00:00:46,041
Ah!

15
00:00:46,041 --> 00:00:48,583
[fighting sounds]

16
00:00:48,791 --> 00:00:51,458
[music playing]

17
00:00:51,458 --> 00:00:57,916
♪ ♪

18
00:00:57,916 --> 00:00:59,166
Oh!

19
00:01:00,416 --> 00:01:02,291
Ah!

20
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:03,583
[groans]

21
00:01:03,791 --> 00:01:07,750
♪ ♪

22
00:01:10,833 --> 00:01:13,333
Please, listen to me!

23
00:01:13,333 --> 00:01:15,458
[smashes]

24
00:01:17,125 --> 00:01:18,625
Let it go.

25
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:20,625
What do you think you can do?

26
00:01:20,625 --> 00:01:21,583
Oh!

27
00:01:21,791 --> 00:01:25,875
♪ ♪

28
00:01:25,875 --> 00:01:27,750
Ah!

29
00:01:28,166 --> 00:01:29,458
Ah!

30
00:01:29,666 --> 00:01:31,041
[kicking]

31
00:01:31,250 --> 00:01:38,416
♪ ♪

32
00:01:40,625 --> 00:01:42,333
Somebody help!

33
00:01:42,333 --> 00:01:45,000
[whoosh]

34
00:01:46,708 --> 00:01:48,000
Who are you?

35
00:01:49,750 --> 00:01:52,625
[music playing]

36
00:01:52,833 --> 00:01:59,708
♪ ♪

37
00:02:00,458 --> 00:02:02,333
Electrowave tackle!

38
00:02:02,541 --> 00:02:03,625
Ah!

39
00:02:06,333 --> 00:02:08,041
Spider-Man!

40
00:02:10,875 --> 00:02:12,875
Mitsuba!

41
00:02:14,333 --> 00:02:16,875
This looks pretty bad.

42
00:02:17,083 --> 00:02:18,625
Nothing we can't handle.

43
00:02:20,750 --> 00:02:23,500
[theme music]

44
00:02:23,708 --> 00:02:28,416
♪ ♪

45
00:02:28,625 --> 00:02:30,333
[singing]

46
00:02:30,333 --> 00:02:37,625
♪ ♪

47
00:03:51,166 --> 00:03:54,458
[music playing]

48
00:03:54,666 --> 00:03:57,000
♪ ♪

49
00:03:57,208 --> 00:04:00,291
Yee! Yee!

50
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:05,500
♪ ♪

51
00:04:05,708 --> 00:04:07,333
[singing]

52
00:04:07,541 --> 00:04:13,875
♪ ♪

53
00:04:14,583 --> 00:04:16,166
It's my turn!

54
00:04:20,041 --> 00:04:21,333
Let's go.

55
00:04:21,541 --> 00:04:24,333
[fighting sounds in background]

56
00:04:24,541 --> 00:04:26,375
Hey, come back.

57
00:04:29,458 --> 00:04:31,166
Don't go yet.

58
00:04:31,166 --> 00:04:34,583
I mean, we've finally
been reunited.

59
00:04:34,791 --> 00:04:36,291
[spits]

60
00:04:37,166 --> 00:04:39,583
You boys are leaving already?

61
00:04:41,125 --> 00:04:43,708
You really should
have stayed down.

62
00:04:43,916 --> 00:04:45,416
Uh--

63
00:04:47,166 --> 00:04:48,458
Quick!
Get away!

64
00:04:48,666 --> 00:04:49,708
This is your chance!

65
00:04:49,708 --> 00:04:51,291
We'll keep them distracted.

66
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:52,708
But hurry!

67
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:56,916
[crying]

68
00:04:57,125 --> 00:04:59,875
[music playing]

69
00:05:00,083 --> 00:05:01,750
You're all alive.

70
00:05:01,958 --> 00:05:03,625
I still can't believe it.

71
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:07,875
♪ ♪

72
00:05:08,083 --> 00:05:13,166
You three risked everything
for a scumbag like me.

73
00:05:15,583 --> 00:05:17,291
I owe you my life.

74
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:24,041
♪ ♪

75
00:05:24,250 --> 00:05:26,041
You guys are my brothers.

76
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:29,000
I need you!

77
00:05:33,208 --> 00:05:40,125
.44 Magnum!

78
00:05:43,166 --> 00:05:45,416
[whack]

79
00:05:46,708 --> 00:05:48,125
[whoosh]

80
00:05:48,125 --> 00:05:49,916
Ah!

81
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,208
Ah!

82
00:05:55,875 --> 00:05:57,416
Ah!

83
00:06:00,500 --> 00:06:02,750
[whack]

84
00:06:03,416 --> 00:06:06,625
Ah!

85
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:10,291
♪ ♪

86
00:06:10,291 --> 00:06:13,000
[gasping]

87
00:06:15,166 --> 00:06:17,166
Are you OK?

88
00:06:17,375 --> 00:06:19,833
Yeah, I'm good.

89
00:06:19,833 --> 00:06:22,291
All done over here.

90
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:23,291
Oh, man.

91
00:06:23,291 --> 00:06:24,458
They kicked your ass.

92
00:06:24,666 --> 00:06:26,125
Can you walk?

93
00:06:26,333 --> 00:06:27,125
Sure.

94
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:28,416
No sweat.

95
00:06:29,583 --> 00:06:31,833
Now let's go beat that monster.

96
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:33,833
Ah!

97
00:06:33,833 --> 00:06:35,750
It-- it's you!

98
00:06:35,958 --> 00:06:37,041
Huh?

99
00:06:38,708 --> 00:06:40,291
Good to see you.

100
00:06:41,458 --> 00:06:43,000
That punch,

101
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:46,166
the moment it landed,
it woke me up!

102
00:06:46,375 --> 00:06:49,125
[crying]

103
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:53,833
I'm so-- so sorry!

104
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:55,500
I know.

105
00:06:56,458 --> 00:06:58,833
[ALL] We're sorry
we hurt you, Boss.

106
00:06:58,833 --> 00:07:01,416
Please forgive us!

107
00:07:01,416 --> 00:07:03,291
[crying]

108
00:07:03,291 --> 00:07:10,125
♪ ♪

109
00:07:10,333 --> 00:07:12,916
[NAKAO] I'm the one
who should apologize.

110
00:07:13,125 --> 00:07:14,583
Huh?

111
00:07:14,791 --> 00:07:18,000
It's my fault
you wound up here.

112
00:07:18,208 --> 00:07:20,541
Sorry I left you behind.

113
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:22,125
Won't happen again.

114
00:07:22,833 --> 00:07:26,333
[ALL]
Ah!

115
00:07:26,708 --> 00:07:28,458
We're OK!

116
00:07:28,708 --> 00:07:30,708
Ah!

117
00:07:33,208 --> 00:07:34,458
Hmm.

118
00:07:36,166 --> 00:07:38,583
What's going on?

119
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:41,583
His love for his friends
broke Shocker's control.

120
00:07:41,791 --> 00:07:43,833
I'm sorry, but this
will have to wait.

121
00:07:44,041 --> 00:07:46,000
We need to move now.

122
00:07:46,208 --> 00:07:47,000
Right.

123
00:07:47,208 --> 00:07:48,041
Hmm!

124
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:49,458
Let us show you the way.

125
00:07:50,625 --> 00:07:52,875
[music playing]

126
00:07:53,083 --> 00:07:54,125
Hey.

127
00:07:54,125 --> 00:07:55,166
Huh?

128
00:07:55,375 --> 00:07:56,666
I've been thinking about it.

129
00:07:56,666 --> 00:07:59,000
We're supposed to wait
for the show's climax.

130
00:07:59,208 --> 00:08:01,208
That's super boring.

131
00:08:01,416 --> 00:08:02,500
Yeah, you're right.

132
00:08:02,708 --> 00:08:04,166
I mean, it's a good plan,

133
00:08:04,375 --> 00:08:06,833
but I'd rather be
fighting Shocker now.

134
00:08:06,833 --> 00:08:10,166
Mitsuba, how dare you
make me wait another second

135
00:08:10,375 --> 00:08:12,208
to avenge our grandparents!

136
00:08:12,416 --> 00:08:13,916
We should have gone
straight for the Batman

137
00:08:14,125 --> 00:08:17,416
instead of sneaking around
like rats on the damn roof.

138
00:08:17,625 --> 00:08:19,416
[MAN] How about you
two fight me then?

139
00:08:19,625 --> 00:08:20,500
[BOTH]
Huh?

140
00:08:20,708 --> 00:08:23,208
[music playing]

141
00:08:23,416 --> 00:08:24,750
♪ ♪

142
00:08:24,958 --> 00:08:25,833
No way.

143
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:28,125
It's you, the Spider-Man!

144
00:08:28,125 --> 00:08:29,125
Yeah, sure.

145
00:08:29,125 --> 00:08:30,125
Let's do it.

146
00:08:30,125 --> 00:08:31,541
Get ready to fight.

147
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:32,541
Ah!

148
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:34,458
Rider!

149
00:08:34,666 --> 00:08:36,208
Machine V3-yah!

150
00:08:36,416 --> 00:08:37,833
- I was kidding.
- Huh?

151
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:38,833
Oh.

152
00:08:39,041 --> 00:08:40,125
[laughs]

153
00:08:40,125 --> 00:08:42,125
You guys really
are entertaining.

154
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:43,583
I'll give you that much to you.

155
00:08:43,791 --> 00:08:46,208
[growls]

156
00:08:46,416 --> 00:08:49,416
Can't wait to see
how this turns out.

157
00:08:49,416 --> 00:08:51,041
[shimmering]

158
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:52,041
Huh?

159
00:08:52,250 --> 00:08:53,416
He vanished?

160
00:08:55,125 --> 00:08:57,041
Yee!

161
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:04,875
Ah!

162
00:09:05,083 --> 00:09:08,125
[music playing]

163
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,500
Nice work.

164
00:09:10,708 --> 00:09:14,500
It's not easy to transform
without the brainwashing.

165
00:09:14,708 --> 00:09:16,583
Well, we learned
from the best.

166
00:09:17,708 --> 00:09:19,125
Almost there!

167
00:09:19,125 --> 00:09:20,666
[thud]

168
00:09:22,291 --> 00:09:23,541
Oh!

169
00:09:24,333 --> 00:09:25,750
[thud]

170
00:09:25,958 --> 00:09:27,958
I've been expecting you.

171
00:09:28,166 --> 00:09:29,250
Mm!

172
00:09:29,625 --> 00:09:30,958
Ah!

173
00:09:31,166 --> 00:09:32,500
Uh, Raiko.

174
00:09:32,708 --> 00:09:33,541
Oh!

175
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:35,291
Wait. Hold on a sec.

176
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:36,625
What are you?

177
00:09:36,833 --> 00:09:38,458
[thud]

178
00:09:38,708 --> 00:09:40,416
Mm.

179
00:09:40,416 --> 00:09:43,625
So, Raiko, tell me,

180
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:47,833
is there a chance you
aren't brainwashed anymore?

181
00:09:48,041 --> 00:09:50,666
I mean, all that time
we spent together.

182
00:09:50,875 --> 00:09:52,708
It had to mean
something, right?

183
00:09:52,916 --> 00:09:53,708
Come on.

184
00:09:53,916 --> 00:09:56,541
[music playing]

185
00:09:56,750 --> 00:10:03,875
♪ ♪

186
00:10:06,875 --> 00:10:09,125
My feelings haven't changed.

187
00:10:11,166 --> 00:10:12,291
I love you.

188
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:14,041
Ah!

189
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:17,166
[ALL]
The hell was that?

190
00:10:17,375 --> 00:10:18,708
Ah!

191
00:10:18,916 --> 00:10:21,041
[crash]

192
00:10:21,250 --> 00:10:23,458
[ALL]
Boss, just hold on!

193
00:10:23,666 --> 00:10:27,833
[RAIKO] It seems that man
has made traitors of you too.

194
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:29,583
[ALL]
Ah!

195
00:10:29,791 --> 00:10:32,333
I have no choice
but to kill you all.

196
00:10:32,541 --> 00:10:33,708
Mm!

197
00:10:33,916 --> 00:10:35,875
Leave her to me.

198
00:10:36,083 --> 00:10:38,625
Take the others
and keep moving.

199
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:39,958
I'll catch up.

200
00:10:41,041 --> 00:10:42,291
Oh!

201
00:10:43,416 --> 00:10:45,583
Don't take too long.

202
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:48,916
Now die!

203
00:10:49,125 --> 00:10:50,541
[ALL]
Ah!

204
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:57,250
♪ ♪

205
00:11:02,666 --> 00:11:04,083
Ah!

206
00:11:04,291 --> 00:11:06,041
Right behind you.

207
00:11:06,250 --> 00:11:07,083
Huh?

208
00:11:07,291 --> 00:11:10,208
[music playing]

209
00:11:12,416 --> 00:11:14,208
You know, you're the one
I was most interested

210
00:11:14,416 --> 00:11:16,250
in going up against.

211
00:11:16,458 --> 00:11:18,041
You're a pro wrestler.

212
00:11:18,250 --> 00:11:20,416
How about a revenge match?

213
00:11:20,625 --> 00:11:22,500
[laughs]

214
00:11:22,708 --> 00:11:25,291
This time, I'm going to hit
you till you stop fighting.

215
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:27,416
I hope that's OK with you.

216
00:11:29,541 --> 00:11:31,333
You're welcome to try.

217
00:11:31,541 --> 00:11:34,291
♪ ♪

218
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:38,000
Ah!

219
00:11:38,208 --> 00:11:40,625
♪ ♪

220
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:44,916
It looks like we've both
improved since our last fight.

221
00:11:45,125 --> 00:11:46,291
That works for me.

222
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:49,083
♪ ♪

223
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:50,416
[knocking]

224
00:11:50,625 --> 00:11:51,875
[HENCHMAN]
Master Bat-Man,

225
00:11:52,083 --> 00:11:53,500
it's almost time.

226
00:11:53,708 --> 00:11:56,958
[laughs]

227
00:11:57,166 --> 00:11:59,375
[shimmering]

228
00:12:02,458 --> 00:12:04,708
[shimmering]

229
00:12:07,625 --> 00:12:09,916
[cheers, applause]

230
00:12:13,041 --> 00:12:15,916
[music playing]

231
00:12:16,125 --> 00:12:23,250
♪ ♪

232
00:12:29,375 --> 00:12:31,291
[singing]

233
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:32,583
[crowd chanting, "hey"]

234
00:12:32,791 --> 00:12:39,875
♪ ♪

235
00:12:42,291 --> 00:12:45,083
[NAKAO] Love is
an amazing thing, huh?

236
00:12:45,291 --> 00:12:46,541
[BOTH]
Huh?

237
00:12:46,541 --> 00:12:49,416
There's a few things
out there that I love,

238
00:12:49,625 --> 00:12:51,916
a handful of great people, too.

239
00:12:52,125 --> 00:12:53,708
Just thinking
about that stuff's

240
00:12:53,916 --> 00:12:56,916
enough to make me feel
like I'm on cloud nine.

241
00:12:59,083 --> 00:13:02,666
And you, you just love
the hell out of pro wrestling,

242
00:13:02,875 --> 00:13:04,041
don't you?

243
00:13:04,250 --> 00:13:05,333
Mm!

244
00:13:05,541 --> 00:13:06,625
Ah.

245
00:13:06,833 --> 00:13:08,083
What's going on here?

246
00:13:08,291 --> 00:13:09,541
Do you two know each other?

247
00:13:09,750 --> 00:13:10,833
We don't.

248
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:17,666
But this old man
taught me something.

249
00:13:17,875 --> 00:13:19,083
Oh!

250
00:13:20,166 --> 00:13:22,708
Even a combatant can
get stronger as long

251
00:13:22,916 --> 00:13:24,958
as they train hard enough.

252
00:13:25,166 --> 00:13:26,250
Ah!

253
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:29,583
That's my Raiko!

254
00:13:31,083 --> 00:13:34,666
I may still just
be a lowly combatant.

255
00:13:34,875 --> 00:13:35,875
No way!

256
00:13:36,083 --> 00:13:37,666
What is this pressure?

257
00:13:37,875 --> 00:13:41,458
[RAIKO] But I can become
stronger than a monster.

258
00:13:43,083 --> 00:13:44,333
Ah!

259
00:13:45,458 --> 00:13:46,458
Ah!

260
00:13:46,666 --> 00:13:48,750
[music playing]

261
00:13:48,958 --> 00:13:51,000
Ah!

262
00:13:52,125 --> 00:13:56,875
My body, it won't listen!

263
00:13:57,083 --> 00:13:58,916
I can't move!

264
00:14:00,708 --> 00:14:03,333
Raiko!

265
00:14:03,708 --> 00:14:06,833
[guffaws]

266
00:14:07,458 --> 00:14:08,916
Ah!

267
00:14:10,375 --> 00:14:14,375
You really did enjoy all
that training we did together.

268
00:14:14,583 --> 00:14:19,208
You actually care about me!

269
00:14:21,916 --> 00:14:26,333
Ha, Raiko, I love
you so damn much!

270
00:14:26,541 --> 00:14:28,875
[slam]

271
00:14:29,083 --> 00:14:31,083
[laughs]

272
00:14:32,916 --> 00:14:34,333
[thud]

273
00:14:37,291 --> 00:14:39,625
Did that finally shut you up?

274
00:14:40,875 --> 00:14:44,541
Uh, just checking in.

275
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:46,125
I can't tell now.

276
00:14:46,333 --> 00:14:48,208
Are you sure you're
still our enemy?

277
00:14:48,416 --> 00:14:49,583
Definitely.

278
00:14:49,583 --> 00:14:52,875
OK, but this whole
"I love you" thing?

279
00:14:53,083 --> 00:14:54,041
Ah!

280
00:14:54,250 --> 00:14:55,583
I'll kill you!

281
00:14:55,791 --> 00:14:57,708
Ah!

282
00:14:57,916 --> 00:14:58,750
Ah!

283
00:14:58,958 --> 00:15:00,041
Mm!

284
00:15:00,250 --> 00:15:01,291
Ah!

285
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:03,916
[music playing]

286
00:15:04,166 --> 00:15:05,166
Ah!

287
00:15:05,375 --> 00:15:07,041
[crash]

288
00:15:07,250 --> 00:15:09,583
♪ ♪

289
00:15:09,791 --> 00:15:11,500
[fighting sounds]

290
00:15:13,333 --> 00:15:14,250
Ah!

291
00:15:14,458 --> 00:15:20,583
♪ ♪

292
00:15:21,541 --> 00:15:23,375
Ah!

293
00:15:25,250 --> 00:15:27,041
Time for a Rainmaker!

294
00:15:27,250 --> 00:15:34,375
♪ ♪

295
00:15:40,833 --> 00:15:45,458
The move I've worked so hard
to perfect is faster!

296
00:15:45,666 --> 00:15:49,458
[intense music]

297
00:15:49,666 --> 00:15:54,958
♪ ♪

298
00:15:55,166 --> 00:15:58,708
Ultimate Electrowave Throw!

299
00:15:58,916 --> 00:15:59,666
Ah!

300
00:15:59,875 --> 00:16:03,625
♪ ♪

301
00:16:03,833 --> 00:16:05,583
[gasping]

302
00:16:05,791 --> 00:16:08,458
[singing]

303
00:16:08,666 --> 00:16:11,458
♪ ♪

304
00:16:11,666 --> 00:16:13,291
[whimpering]

305
00:16:14,125 --> 00:16:17,458
Uh, unbelievable.

306
00:16:18,791 --> 00:16:21,833
You countered
Kazuchika Okada's Rainmaker

307
00:16:22,041 --> 00:16:26,041
with a version
of Naoya Ogawa's STO.

308
00:16:26,250 --> 00:16:28,250
[shimmering]

309
00:16:29,916 --> 00:16:32,458
That move was my own.

310
00:16:33,666 --> 00:16:35,666
[cheers]

311
00:16:35,875 --> 00:16:38,541
[music playing]

312
00:16:38,750 --> 00:16:45,875
♪ ♪

313
00:16:55,958 --> 00:17:02,750
[RAIKO]
I lost again to a human.

314
00:17:03,458 --> 00:17:05,000
Not even Shocker.

315
00:17:05,208 --> 00:17:07,666
[music playing]

316
00:17:07,875 --> 00:17:10,000
♪ ♪

317
00:17:10,208 --> 00:17:13,750
No, it wasn't just her.

318
00:17:13,958 --> 00:17:17,333
It was the power that came
from her unshakable commitment

319
00:17:17,541 --> 00:17:19,000
to her beliefs.

320
00:17:19,208 --> 00:17:22,666
Her strength lies
in her resolve.

321
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:25,875
She was more
determined than I was.

322
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,791
Amazing.

323
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:33,666
I see now,
I want to be stronger.

324
00:17:33,875 --> 00:17:41,333
♪ ♪

325
00:17:44,416 --> 00:17:45,416
Radio check.

326
00:17:45,625 --> 00:17:47,125
Are you in position?

327
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:48,875
I'm ready.

328
00:17:49,083 --> 00:17:50,291
So am I.

329
00:17:50,500 --> 00:17:51,875
All set.

330
00:17:52,083 --> 00:17:53,625
Just say the word.

331
00:17:53,833 --> 00:17:56,416
[YURIKO]
Looks like
I'm just in time.

332
00:17:56,625 --> 00:17:58,125
I'm glad you made it!

333
00:17:58,333 --> 00:17:59,125
Nice work.

334
00:17:59,333 --> 00:18:00,375
You beat her?

335
00:18:00,583 --> 00:18:01,958
Yep.

336
00:18:02,166 --> 00:18:02,958
Let's do it.

337
00:18:03,166 --> 00:18:05,833
[music playing]

338
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:08,541
[fireworks]

339
00:18:08,750 --> 00:18:12,250
[cheers, applause]

340
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:20,125
[light flash]

341
00:18:20,333 --> 00:18:24,000
Everyone, thank you
so much for coming today.

342
00:18:24,208 --> 00:18:26,708
And now for the grand finale.

343
00:18:26,916 --> 00:18:30,000
We have a gift to share
with our beloved fans.

344
00:18:30,208 --> 00:18:31,958
[cheers, applause]

345
00:18:33,041 --> 00:18:35,041
[beeping]

346
00:18:35,250 --> 00:18:39,000
[music and vocalizations]

347
00:18:39,208 --> 00:18:46,333
♪ ♪

348
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:04,500
Cut the lights!

349
00:19:04,708 --> 00:19:06,708
[light thuds]

350
00:19:08,375 --> 00:19:10,541
[sirens and screaming]

351
00:19:14,916 --> 00:19:16,166
A fire?

352
00:19:17,666 --> 00:19:19,458
[WOMAN]
Emergency announcement.

353
00:19:19,666 --> 00:19:21,250
Emergency announcement.

354
00:19:21,458 --> 00:19:23,166
A fire has broken out.

355
00:19:23,375 --> 00:19:25,375
The concert will not continue.

356
00:19:25,583 --> 00:19:29,375
For your own safety,
follow all staff instructions.

357
00:19:29,583 --> 00:19:31,000
Evacuate.

358
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:34,166
Proceed to the nearest
exit in an orderly fashion.

359
00:19:34,375 --> 00:19:37,625
I will repeat,
emergency announcement.

360
00:19:37,833 --> 00:19:39,208
Everyone, please stay calm!

361
00:19:39,416 --> 00:19:41,208
Walking is safer
than running!

362
00:19:41,416 --> 00:19:42,833
Make sure to not
lock the doors.

363
00:19:43,041 --> 00:19:44,666
Leave space for others
when you exit.

364
00:19:44,875 --> 00:19:47,000
This way, please.

365
00:19:48,416 --> 00:19:50,000
What is this?

366
00:19:50,208 --> 00:19:51,541
Do not let them escape.

367
00:19:51,750 --> 00:19:52,958
[ALL]
Sir!

368
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:55,375
Yee!

369
00:19:55,708 --> 00:19:57,333
Yee!

370
00:19:57,666 --> 00:19:59,333
Yee!

371
00:20:00,041 --> 00:20:01,666
[NAKAO]
I don't think so!

372
00:20:03,541 --> 00:20:05,750
[fireworks]

373
00:20:06,333 --> 00:20:07,750
Ah!

374
00:20:07,958 --> 00:20:10,208
[screaming]

375
00:20:10,416 --> 00:20:11,750
My Raiko!

376
00:20:11,958 --> 00:20:13,875
I'm going to get
you out of this.

377
00:20:14,083 --> 00:20:16,416
Even if I have to take
the boss's head.

378
00:20:16,625 --> 00:20:18,916
Tojima and Ichiyo,
you're up!

379
00:20:19,125 --> 00:20:22,458
[music playing]

380
00:20:22,666 --> 00:20:24,000
Huh?

381
00:20:26,333 --> 00:20:28,250
Let's do this, Shocker!

382
00:20:28,458 --> 00:20:34,875
♪ ♪

383
00:20:35,083 --> 00:20:36,041
What the hell?

384
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:43,083
♪ ♪

385
00:20:43,875 --> 00:20:50,791
[BOTH]
Now Rider Double Kick!

386
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:52,291
Ah!

387
00:20:53,375 --> 00:20:56,250
[crashes]

388
00:20:56,458 --> 00:20:57,791
[ALL]
Did they hurt you, Master?

389
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,458
Who the hell are you?

390
00:21:00,666 --> 00:21:01,875
I'm V3.

391
00:21:02,083 --> 00:21:03,958
I'm Kamen Rider!

392
00:21:04,166 --> 00:21:06,250
And we've come to stop you.

393
00:21:06,458 --> 00:21:08,958
Your evil scheme
ends here, Shocker!

394
00:21:09,166 --> 00:21:10,875
[shimmering]

395
00:21:11,083 --> 00:21:18,208
♪ ♪

396
00:21:20,791 --> 00:21:23,083
You idiots ruined everything.

397
00:21:24,333 --> 00:21:26,166
[growling]

398
00:21:26,375 --> 00:21:33,500
♪ ♪

399
00:21:38,458 --> 00:21:40,250
I'm going to kill you all.

400
00:21:40,458 --> 00:21:43,000
[singing]

401
00:21:43,208 --> 00:21:45,791
♪ ♪

402
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:47,375
Well, well.

403
00:21:47,583 --> 00:21:49,125
Impressive.

404
00:21:50,375 --> 00:21:57,333
However, with these odds,
do you think you can survive?

405
00:21:59,083 --> 00:22:02,291
[theme music]

406
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:05,416
[singing]

407
00:22:05,625 --> 00:22:12,750
♪ ♪
